{"parse":{"title":"CO2 (opera)","pageid":20346435,"revid":830677303,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-style: italic;\">CO2</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-weight: bold;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Opera\" title=\"Opera\">Opera</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Giorgio_Battistelli\" title=\"Giorgio Battistelli\">Giorgio Battistelli</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Librettist</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Carsen\" title=\"Robert Carsen\">Robert Carsen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Based on</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/wiki/An_Inconvenient_Truth\" title=\"An Inconvenient Truth\">An Inconvenient Truth</a></i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Premiere</th><td>\n<span class=\"vevent\">16&#160;May&#160;2015<span style=\"display:none\">&#160;(<span class=\"bday dtstart published updated\">2015-05-16</span>)</span><br /><span class=\"summary\"><a href=\"/wiki/La_Scala\" title=\"La Scala\">La Scala</a></span></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>CO<small>2</small></b></i> is an Italian opera by <a href=\"/wiki/Giorgio_Battistelli\" title=\"Giorgio Battistelli\">Giorgio Battistelli</a> which premiered at <a href=\"/wiki/La_Scala\" title=\"La Scala\">La Scala</a> on May 16, 2015.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ft.com_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ft.com-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is based on <a href=\"/wiki/Al_Gore\" title=\"Al Gore\">Al Gore</a>'s documentary <i><a href=\"/wiki/An_Inconvenient_Truth\" title=\"An Inconvenient Truth\">An Inconvenient Truth</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dammann_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Dammann-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and Gore was initially a character in the opera.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ft.com_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ft.com-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The libretto, primarily in English but containing passages in other languages, was written by <a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Carsen\" title=\"Robert Carsen\">Robert Carsen</a>, who directed the production, and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ian_Burton&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ian Burton (page does not exist)\">Ian Burton</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ft.com_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ft.com-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=CO2_(opera)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ft.com-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ft.com_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ft.com_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ft.com_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/491bb518-f7d6-11e4-8bd5-00144feab7de.html#axzz3aN5sq3LT\">\"When opera takes on the big issues\"</a>. <i>Financial Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 May</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Financial+Times&amp;rft.atitle=When+opera+takes+on+the+big+issues&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fintl%2Fcms%2Fs%2F0%2F491bb518-f7d6-11e4-8bd5-00144feab7de.html%23axzz3aN5sq3LT&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%